  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Full 13-factor assessment completed. Decision recorded as Accepted with assurance level Medium; however, multiple credibility factors show achieved levels below required levels, constituting a structural inconsistency that triggers COMPOUND-03.",
