      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation setup review by a qualified independent analyst; checklist-based confirmation that boundary conditions, material properties, and solver settings match the approved simulation plan.",
      "rationale": "Internal peer review of simulation setup was conducted but was performed by a team member rather than an independent analyst; no formal checklist was used. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form selection must be justified through sensitivity studies comparing at least two turbulence closure models and two hemolysis damage models; selected form must demonstrate lowest bias against experimental data.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on prior literature; no comparative sensitivity study between turbulence closures was performed for this specific pump geometry. Hemolysis damage model selection was not formally justified. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must be identified, sourced from traceable measurements or literature, and propagated through Monte Carlo UQ to bound their contribution to output uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed covering fluid viscosity, density, and pump rotational speed. Red blood cell mechanical properties (critical inputs to the hemolysis model) were drawn from literature without experimental characterization for the specific blood analogue used. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
